asset.name: Genesis Wallet
asset.description:
Genesis Wallet  - I can’t believe it’s been 5 years since I got into the Blockchain space and now here I am, witnessing and proudly taking part in one of the most incredible leap in the merging of technology and art. The future of the internet, and society, is being created now, by everyone building and contributing to these new platforms and tools.

While some argue against it entirely, due to the high power consumption of the underlying technology. We must keep in mind the teams behind Ethereum, along with other blockchains, are hard at work everyday to create new scalability solutions to reduce congestion and create a more optimized systems.

These are temporary issues, and I strongly believe that we must recognize and leverage them on a personal level, while keeping in mind that this technology will provide much more solutions than problems in the long term. 

We’re in demand for higher computation and power usage regardless of Blockchain.
The goal should not be to hinder or cancel the development of these technologies and shame their communities, but instead to transition to more sustainable energy sources to power them in the first place.

@cyrusjameskhan

asset.name: Zen Monk 3
asset.description:
This is a digital painting of Taisen Deshimaru a Soto Zen teacher from the 20th century. Sitting zazen is done for hours at a time without even the slightest twitch. The mind opens to all of the senses simultaneously including keeping the eyes open. Once the mind is calm one is able to feel a sense of stillness and oneness with time and the ever-changing present moment. 

This piece is showing that exact moment when the stillness hits. This is a glimpse of life that many people will never see. I regard practicing zen meditation as a key to living the best life possible in a world filled with sleeping zombies. 

I have painted this in Procreate.

asset.name: XCOPY-YuraMiron effect
asset.description:
We’ve created this collaboration piece purely for our own fun & published it on Tumblr on August 22 in 2012 https://xcopy.tumblr.com/post/29935634610/xcopy-vs-miron

6 years later in 2018 XCOPY was one of the first artists who have recognized the power of cryptoart. An OG, super talented, supportive/great person!

I’ve joined cryptoart in the late 2018 and started my path as cryptoartist.

On March 26 2021 XCOPY has bought 2 artworks of mine from the secondary market on SupeRare and wrote a tweet saying: “cryptoart OG @YuraMironArt 1/1s going for an absolute  steal” https://twitter.com/XCOPYART/status/1375550272429232134

It went viral and many of my pieces have been collected from the secondary market as well as directly from myself.

From the bottom of my heart I’m grateful for every single collector for believing in me and supporting my evolution as an artist.

‘XCOPY-YuraMiron effect’ is an experiential approach of building up an artist’s path, style, communicating the message, connecting with artists, collectors, platforms, curators. 
This effect can happen only to dedicated ones who continue to adapt and reflect, to create and decompose, to communicate and build for many years. 
 
Today, almost 9 years after our first collaboration we’ve minted it and distributed it to a copy to all collectors who have bought 1/1 art from me directly or on the secondary market on SuperRare, MakersPlace, & KnownOrigin after XCOPY’s viral tweet 4 days ago until this artdrop to collectors: KeyboardMonkey, Hyperspek, Ethnm55555, 0xnostoca, Niftyt, Jmortesq, 0xbrain, Krunk395, Steamrollers, Supahmarbler, The Alchemist, Ethnm55555, Thnarth, Gorare, EpikDrop, Jperlin, Honupower, Zaidkirdsey, Soso, Krypyarupya, Mrbuxl, Shinjiakhirah, Rantumbits, Tony, Jay, GMoney, Freightrain, Bblockchain James.

The last edition is up for an auction for 24 hours to cover the gas fees of minting and distributing this artdrop. 

Loving, Yura Miron

asset.name: Aphrodite (Yellow - animated)
asset.description:
Title: Aphrodite (Yellow - animated)
Artist: Ola Volo
Edition: /3
Medium: mp4

“Aphrodite (Yellow - animated)” is from an edition of 3 animated NFT artworks as part of a series of four variations. Two colours (blue & yellow), each available as still and animated variations.

In this animated version, the Rose opens and closes while Aphrodite blinks.

Ola Volo portrays her Goddess in a relaxed, yet elegant manner, daintily holding a rose, a symbol of passion and love. Aphrodite gazes across the horizon, perhaps in search of a lost lover, or, anticipating the return of a dear companion.

Roses have been used for thousands of years to convey messages without words and Ola cleverly uses this imagery to evoke thought, and communicate with her viewer.

Aphrodite's history is told through the rich tapestry of her cloak. She is in touch with the land yet reigns over the Universe.

Happy Collecting!

asset.name: new_fragments_of_post_capitalist_life_02
asset.description: The original fragments series featured scrambled pixels from the likes of Raphael, Brueghel, Winterhalter. The concept was that the past, for most modern people, only exists as little bits of flavor and color - and the true substance and meaning of it is lost on us. This new series has more complex compositions and living strokes to tie them together - featuring pixels from modern consumerist brands or older artwork that has been transformed with palettes and Processing algorithms totally alien to the original context. In this sense, this is also a way the past survives - unrecognizably updated and projected-upon by the present. This second piece features some samples from Constable - but all with acid yellow, mauve, tan and black palettes that would shock his sensibilities. These are the new fragments for people living in a world indifferent to consumerism and capitalism but still adorned with it.

This is the third exploration of a world where Andy Warhol is alive and augmented, and he apparently makes designs using program-generated patterns in an evolution of his Amiga designs. Dispensing with the traditional frame, I'm trying to explore new shapes and compositions that are impossible or inappropriate for other movements. I've expanded the cyborg_warhol program to include new shapes and stroke patterns, and these compositions use asynchronous frame rates for the patterns whereas before they were uniform.
The threshold designs on these pieces are meant to call to mind Warhol's screen prints - his factory prints - and hence the name "cyborg_warhol_factory_print" - these designs combine a new permutation of Warhol-esque things.

asset.name: Mon Amour
asset.description: “How to appreciate the beauty of a woman: First, close your eyes without any lust or sexual desire, then feel the softness of her body, her delicate hands, her eyes, her lips, her breasts, her thighs. Second, soak your soul in her mind, feel the vortex of her inner needs and desires, listen to the rhythmic sound of her joys and sorrows, and tiptoe on the matrix of her dreams and longings. As soon as you imagine and understand these nuances in a woman, you’ll immediately feel a strange sensation of warmth and nurturing presence, almost maternal, like a gentle breeze in the sea or the fragrance of flowers in the forest. You see, her beauty does not reside in her physical appearance—whoever she is and no matter how she looks—because she, the woman herself, is the definition, the embodiment, and the birthplace of beauty. (Danny Castillones Sillada, The Phenomenology of Beauty in a Woman)”

asset.name: XCOPY-YuraMiron effect
asset.description:
We’ve created this collaboration piece purely for our own fun & published it on Tumblr on August 22 in 2012 https://xcopy.tumblr.com/post/29935634610/xcopy-vs-miron

6 years later in 2018 XCOPY was one of the first artists who have recognized the power of cryptoart. An OG, super talented, supportive/great person!

I’ve joined cryptoart in the late 2018 and started my path as cryptoartist.

On March 26 2021 XCOPY has bought 2 artworks of mine from the secondary market on SupeRare and wrote a tweet saying: “cryptoart OG @YuraMironArt 1/1s going for an absolute  steal” https://twitter.com/XCOPYART/status/1375550272429232134

It went viral and many of my pieces have been collected from the secondary market as well as directly from myself.

From the bottom of my heart I’m grateful for every single collector for believing in me and supporting my evolution as an artist.

‘XCOPY-YuraMiron effect’ is an experiential approach of building up an artist’s path, style, communicating the message, connecting with artists, collectors, platforms, curators. 
This effect can happen only to dedicated ones who continue to adapt and reflect, to create and decompose, to communicate and build for many years. 
 
Today, almost 9 years after our first collaboration we’ve minted it and distributed it to a copy to all collectors who have bought 1/1 art from me directly or on the secondary market on SuperRare, MakersPlace, & KnownOrigin after XCOPY’s viral tweet 4 days ago until this artdrop to collectors: KeyboardMonkey, Hyperspek, Ethnm55555, 0xnostoca, Niftyt, Jmortesq, 0xbrain, Krunk395, Steamrollers, Supahmarbler, The Alchemist, Ethnm55555, Thnarth, Gorare, EpikDrop, Jperlin, Honupower, Zaidkirdsey, Soso, Krypyarupya, Mrbuxl, Shinjiakhirah, Rantumbits, Tony, Jay, GMoney, Freightrain, Bblockchain James.

The last edition is up for an auction for 24 hours to cover the gas fees of minting and distributing this artdrop. 

Loving, Yura Miron

This is the world 'Neeuv' exists in, as she jumps though her most recent portal in the metaverse!

asset.name: HIDE AND SEEK
asset.description:
Created in 2019, HIDE AND SEEK is an ode to what my style has become. Beautiful colors paired with odd / eerie subjects. I have a real fondness for this piece. I think I hit everything I was going for and find myself lost in it at times. 

The original 3D eyeball asset was created by artist Tom Hodes (Sketchfab) and textures were tweaked by myself to pull out the details I was going for.
